<!-- ══════ SIDING TYPES ══════ -->
<section class="siding-types" id="siding-types">
  <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">What We Install</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-title">SIDING<br>OPTIONS</h2>
  <div class="gold-rule"></div>
  <p style="font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ash);max-width:560px;line-height:1.9;">We install and repair a range of exterior siding materials. Each option has its strengths &mdash; we help you choose what makes sense for your home and your budget.</p>

  <div class="siding-types-grid">
    <div class="siding-type-card">
      <span class="siding-type-icon">&#9670;</span>
      <div class="siding-type-name">Vinyl Siding</div>
      <p class="siding-type-desc">The most popular choice for homes across Halifax and Dartmouth. Vinyl siding is low-maintenance, weather-resistant, and available in a wide range of colours and profiles. It handles Nova Scotia's freeze-thaw cycles well and won't rot, peel, or need repainting. An excellent balance of durability and value.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="siding-type-card">
      <span class="siding-type-icon">&#9670;</span>
      <div class="siding-type-name">Composite Siding</div>
      <p class="siding-type-desc">Engineered for performance, composite siding offers the natural appearance of wood with significantly better resistance to moisture and insects. It's a strong choice for homeowners in Bedford, Sackville, and coastal areas of HRM where humidity and salt air accelerate wear on traditional materials.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="siding-type-card">
      <span class="siding-type-icon">&#9670;</span>
      <div class="siding-type-name">Wood Siding</div>
      <p class="siding-type-desc">Classic character that nothing else replicates. Cedar and spruce siding bring warmth and authenticity to heritage homes and custom builds. We handle proper installation with appropriate sealing and ventilation to maximise its lifespan in Nova Scotia's demanding coastal climate.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ══════ WHY ETRA / WEATHER ══════ -->
<section class="why-section">
  <div class="why-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">Built for This Climate</span></div>
      <h2 class="section-title">NOVA SCOTIA<br>WEATHER.<br>HANDLED.</h2>
      <div class="gold-rule"></div>
      <p class="svc-content-body">Halifax homes face conditions that many parts of Canada simply don't deal with &mdash; the combination of ocean moisture, heavy freeze-thaw cycling, and strong coastal winds creates a uniquely demanding environment for any exterior cladding. Siding that works in Ontario won't necessarily hold up here without proper installation technique.</p>
      <p class="svc-content-body">That's where local experience matters. Our crew understands the specific challenges of siding homes in HRM, from the salt air corrosion common in Dartmouth and Eastern Passage to the wind exposure on hilltop properties in Bedford and Hammonds Plains. We don't just hang panels &mdash; we build a weather-tight envelope around your home.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="why-quote">"Your siding is more than a finish &mdash; it's your home's <em>armour against the Atlantic</em>."</p>
      <div class="why-features">
        <div class="why-feat">Proper moisture barriers and housewrap on every install</div>
        <div class="why-feat">Flashing around all windows, doors, and penetrations</div>
        <div class="why-feat">Materials rated for coastal and high-wind zones</div>
        <div class="why-feat">Ventilation detailing to prevent moisture buildup</div>
        <div class="why-feat">Experienced with older Halifax homes and new HRM builds</div>
        <div class="why-feat">Storm damage repair and insurance-related work</div>
      </div>
      <a href="#quote-form" class="btn-gold">Book a Free Assessment &nbsp;&rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- ══════ FAQ ══════ -->
<section class="faq-section">
  <div class="eyebrow"><span class="eyebrow-line"></span><span class="eyebrow-text">Common Questions</span></div>
  <h2 class="section-title">FREQUENTLY<br>ASKED<br>QUESTIONS.</h2>
  <div class="gold-rule"></div>
  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">What types of siding do you install in Halifax?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">We install vinyl siding, composite siding, and wood siding across Halifax and HRM. Vinyl is the most popular choice for Nova Scotia's climate — durable, low-maintenance, and built to handle freeze-thaw cycles and coastal weather.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">How long does exterior siding installation take?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">A typical house siding project takes three to seven days depending on home size, whether existing siding needs removal, and material choice. We'll give you a clear, realistic timeline in your free quote.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Is new siding a good investment in Nova Scotia?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Absolutely. Quality siding protects your home from Halifax's wet, windy winters, improves energy efficiency, and significantly boosts curb appeal and resale value. It's one of the best exterior investments a homeowner can make.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Do you remove old siding before installing new?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes — we remove and dispose of existing siding as part of the project. We inspect the sheathing underneath before installing new material and address any moisture damage we find along the way.</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-q">Do you pull permits for siding projects in Halifax?<span class="faq-icon">+</span></button>
      <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Permit requirements depend on the scope and municipality. We'll advise you on whether your project requires a permit and can assist with the process where needed.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

